HEADWORD: Dementia
<hw>De*men"ti*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr.
<ets>demens</ets>. See <er>Dement</er>.]</ety> <def>Insanity; madness;
esp. that form which consists in weakness or total loss of thought and
reason; mental imbecility; idiocy.</def>⟦br⟧
